# <type>(<optional scope>): <short summary> (72 chars max)
#
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   refactor - Code change that is not a feature or fix
#   perf     - Performance improvement
#   test     - Adding or improving tests
#   docs     - Documentation only
#   chore    - Maintenance, deps, tooling
#   ci       - CI/CD pipeline changes
#   build    - Build system changes
#   style    - Formatting, whitespace (no logic change)
#
# Use ! after type (e.g. feat!) or add BREAKING CHANGE: in the body
# for breaking changes.
#
# Body (optional - explain *what* and *why*, 72 chars per line):
#
#
# Footer (optional - issue refs, BREAKING CHANGE):
# Refs: #123
# BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#
# Activate with: git config commit.template .gitmessage
